item.description:
This amazing walk starts in Washington Square and goes up Aspinwall and Fischer Hill. We will experience beautiful neighborhoods, parks and pathways of stairs.

For those who want to learn more about the pathways we will be walking please visit http://www.brooklinehistoricalsociety.org/history/paths.asp and read about Addington, Colbourne, Rawson and Winthrop Paths.

Additionally, for those who want to learn more about Fischer Hill please visit http://www.brooklinehistoricalsociety.org/history/presComm/fisherHillTest.asp.

We are meeting in front of front of Starbucks. It is located near the Washington Square T Station. There is also parking on Beacon Street.
